  "sphere_commentary": {
    "run_date": "2026-05-11",
    "overview": "The three series demonstrate distinct efficacy profiles aligned with their therapeutic focuses, with HEALING protocols showing consistent outcomes, THRIVING achieving the highest scores, and TRANSFORMING reflecting adaptive challenges. \n• HEALING protocols (n=574) deliver the most stable results (mean=6.98, std=1.77) across all entry points. \n• THRIVING's Focus & Clarity protocols (T-FC-L3: mean=7.63) and Creative Flow protocols show strong efficacy with high positive ratings. \n• TRANSFORMING protocols (n=181) demonstrate expected variability (std=1.87), particularly in ASCENT mood/energy and motivation protocols.",
    "cross_series": "Series performance aligns with protocol design arcs but reveals emerging patterns in cross-priming effects. \n• HEALING's crisis protocols maintain comparable means to anxiety protocols despite higher distress contexts. \n• THRIVING's HOLD-type protocols consistently outperform DESCENT protocols in the same series. \n• TRANSFORMING's Level 3 protocols show significant divergence between predicted and observed scores (e.g., X-MC-L3 predicted 7.538 vs actual 5.7).",
    "anomalies": "Three protocols require prioritized investigation due to response pattern deviations. \n• X-MC-L3 (mean=5.7) underperforms predicted efficacy by 1.83 units with developing confidence. \n• T-FC-L3 (mean=7.63) shows significant bimodal distribution (10/35 scoring 10). \n• H-OS-L1's YouTube views (30) vs missing retention data suggests potential reach-impact mismatch.",
    "development_signals": "Four actionable development priorities emerge from convergent signal analysis: \n• [CONVERGENT SIGNAL] Adjust T-FC-L3 rhythm structure to address 29% 'slightly busy' feedback (3 analyzers). \n• [CONVERGENT SIGNAL] Create X-MD-L1 L2 variant with shortened ASCENT phase (4 analyzers). \n• Investigate H-OS-L1 subgroup effects given bimodal settling time reports (Care-giving:6 vs Therapy:3). \n• Boost visibility of T-FC-L3 via cross-bucket routing recommendations.",
    "embedding_analysis": "Embedding context reveals evolving analytical framing with confidence limitations. \n• CROSS-RUN DRIFT: Significant shifts in H-SL-L1 (sim=0.701) and crisis protocols suggest emerging subgroup effects. \n• CROSS-PROTOCOL SEMANTIC CLUSTERS: Crisis protocols form distinct cluster (sim>0.8), validating design intent. \n• Confidence in drift patterns is moderate due to limited historical runs (2 comparison points).",
